description: Gets a list of key groups. You can optionally specify the maximum number of items to receive in the response. If the total number of items in the list exceeds the maximum that you specify, or the default maximum, the response is paginated. To get the next page of items, send a subsequent request that specifies the NextMarker value from the current response as the Marker value in the subsequent request.

nested_items.name: NextMarker
nested_items.description: If there are more items in the list than are in this response, this element is present. It contains the value that you should use in the Marker field of a subsequent request to continue listing key groups.

nested_items.name: MaxItems
nested_items.description: The maximum number of key groups requested.

nested_items.name: Quantity
nested_items.description: The number of key groups returned in the response.

nested_items.name: Id
nested_items.description: The identifier for the key group.

nested_items.name: LastModifiedTime
nested_items.description: The date and time when the key group was last modified.

nested_items.name: Name
nested_items.description: A name to identify the key group.

nested_items.name: Items
nested_items.description: A list of the identifiers of the public keys in the key group.

nested_items.name: Comment
nested_items.description: A comment to describe the key group. The comment cannot be longer than 128 characters.
